g = @(y,x) a*x;           % linear model for information density

3. Define the Laplacian operator:

laplacian = @(u) (circshift(u,[0 1]) + circshift(u,[0 -1]) + ...
    circshift(u,[1 0]) + circshift(u,[-1 0]) - 4*u) / dx^2;

4. Set up the time stepping loop:

T = 30;    % total simulation time
dt = 0.01; % time step
nt = round(T/dt);  % number of time steps
for i = 1:nt
    % Compute the derivatives
    fy = f(y,x);
    gy = g(y,x);
    ydot = fy + D*laplacian(y);
    hdot = gy + C*laplacian(h);

    % Update the variables
    y = y + dt*ydot;
    h = h + dt*hdot;
end

